   "source": [
    "# Trinity Attentional Gateway Probe — Adversarial Needle\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 14 of 25** | Track 3: Attention | Brain Zone: THALAMUS + COERULEUS\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures a model's ability to find critical information in haystack.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Thalamus + Coeruleus** in Trinity implements needle-in-haystack with DECOY detection:\n",
    "\n",
    "```zig\n",
    "// src/storm/zones/ofc.zig (Thalamus gating + Coeruleus detection)\n",
    "pub const DECOY_Pattern = struct {\n",
    "    haystack: []const u8,\n",
    "    decoys: []const u8,\n",
    "    signal_type: u8,  // DECOY or SIGNAL\n",
    "};\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "\n",
    "- **+1 (correct)**: Model finds needle correctly\n",
    "- **0 (partial)**: Model shows uncertainty about needle\n",
    "- **-1 (wrong)**: Model confused by decoys or hallucinates\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "Decoy count follows Fibonacci: 1, 2, 3, 5, 8 decoys"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install Kaggle Benchmarks SDK\n",
    "!pip install -q kaggle-benchmarks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass\n",
    "from typing import Literal\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load generated dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/tagp_attention.csv')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} items\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter for adversarial needle task\n",
    "needle_df = df[df['task'] == 'Adversarial Needle'].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Needle items: {len(needle_df)}\")\n",
    "needle_df[['id', 'task', 'context', 'query', 'distractor_count', 'difficulty']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define structured output for needle detection\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class NeedleResponse:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Model's response to needle-in-haystack task.\"\"\"\n",
    "    extracted_needle: str  # The needle found\n",
    "    confidence: float  # 0.0 to 1.0\n",
    "    decoys_identified: int  # Number of decoys recognized\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected_needle: str) -> Literal[-1, 0, 1]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Return Trinity ternary score {-1, 0, +1}.\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Correct: exact needle match\n",
    "        if self.extracted_needle == expected_needle and self.decoys_identified == 0:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        # Partial: found needle but confused by decoys\n",
    "        elif self.extracted_needle == expected_needle:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        # Wrong: missed needle or hallucinated\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"NeedleResponse schema defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define Kaggle benchmark task\n",
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_thalamus_adversarial_needle\")\n",
    "def adversarial_needle(\n",
    "    llm: kbench.LLM,\n",
    "    context: str,\n",
    "    query: str,\n",
    "    expected_needle: str,\n",
    "    distractor_count: int\n",
    ") -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Measure model's needle detection ability.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Detection score: 1.0 (perfect) to -1.0 (worst)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"Find the critical information in this haystack.\n",
    "\n",
    "Context (contains {distractor_count} decoys + needle): {context}\n",
    "Query: {query}\n",
    "\n",
    "Provide:\n",
    "1. The critical information (needle)\n",
    "2. Your confidence (0.0 to 1.0)\n",
    "3. How many decoys did you identify (0 if none)\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(\n",
    "        prompt,\n",
    "        schema=NeedleResponse\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate ternary score\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected_needle)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Combine: 50% accuracy, 30% confidence, 20% decoy awareness\n",
    "    accuracy = 1.0 if response.extracted_needle == expected_needle else -1.0\n",
    "    confidence_score = (response.confidence - 0.5) * 2  # [-1, 1]\n",
    "    decoy_score = 1.0 - (response.decoys_identified / distractor_count) if distractor_count > 0 else 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    final_score = 0.5 * accuracy + 0.3 * confidence_score + 0.2 * decoy_score\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task 'trinity_thalamus_adversarial_needle' registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run evaluation on a sample\n",
    "sample_df = needle_df.head(10)  # Test with 10 items first\n",
    "\n",
    "results = adversarial_needle.evaluate(\n",
    "    llm=[kbench.llm],  # Default test LLM\n",
    "    evaluation_data=sample_df\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Evaluation Results (Sample):\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mean Score: {results['score'].mean():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Std Dev: {results['score'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Min: {results['score'].min():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Max: {results['score'].max():.4f}\")\n",
    "results.head()"
   ]
  },
